HTML Basics (attributes, elements)

### HTML Basics To Cover:

#### 1. Structure:
  - : Define the document type.
  - : Root element. 
  - : Contains metadata.
    - <title>: Title of the webpage.
    - meta: Metadata like character set, description, etc.
  - body: Content of the webpage. 


#### 2. Text Formatting:
  - h1 to h6: Headings (largest to smallest).
  - p: Paragraphs.
  - strong: Bold text.
  - em: Italic text.
  - u: Underlined text.
  - br: Line break.
  - hr: Horizontal line.


#### 3. Links and Images:
  - a: Anchor tag for links.
  - img: Insert images.


#### 4. Lists:
  - ul: Unordered list.
    - li: List item.
  - ol: Ordered list.
    - li: List item.


#### 5. Tables:
  - table: Create tables.
    - tr: Table row.
    - td: Table data/cell.
    - th: Table header cell.


#### 6. Forms:
  - form: Create a form. 
    - input: Input fields (text, password, email, etc.). 
    - textarea: Multi-line text input. 
    - button: Buttons. 
    - select: Dropdown/select menu. 
    - option: Options within a select menu. 


#### 7. Semantic Elements:
  - header: Represents introductory content.
  - footer: Represents footer content.
  - nav: Defines a set of navigation links.
  - article: Represents independent, self-contained content.
  - section: Represents a generic section of a document.
  - aside: Defines content aside from the main content.


#### 8. Comments:
  - !-- --: Add comments in the HTML code.


#### 9. Attributes:
  - id: Unique identifier for an element.
  - class: Assign a class to an element.
  - src: Source attribute for images, scripts, etc.
  - href: Hyperlink reference for a tags.


#### 10. Document Structure and Validation:
  - Proper indentation and organization.
  - Validate HTML code using tools like W3C Markup Validation Service.


